# Breadboard Robot
The breadboasrd robot is a simple-as-possible robot that is built using breadboards and 3D printed parts.
- No soldering necessary
- Reference 3D printed parts are available, but students are encouraged to design their own parts
- Students are encouraged to add their own capabilities to the robot. One example is  rubber-band launcher.

## Remote Control robot
Students are walked through how to create a remote control breadkoard robot. This relies on the companion project
breadboard joystick controller. This project uses a callback stratety instead of Object Oriented Programming to keep
thngs simple for students new to Python. The end result for this project is code similar to rc_robot_main.py. The program used the following libraries:
- BLEClient
- Buzzer
- Servo (optional)

## Automonous Robot
The Robot class is designed to allow programming of a robot class for autonomous operation. 
This class is in-process. The attempt is to use an IMU to allow the user to turn specified angles and move forward 
specify locations.

